  "text": "Sign in to your Android Police account A month after its announcement, we're finally getting our hands on the Pixel 9a. And for the most part, the early reviews are fairly positive, making it a great phone to pick up if you're looking for the Pixel experience on a budget. The good news is that, despite its low entry price point of $499, plenty of retailers and wireless carriers are offering discounts on the phone. Related A free Pixel 9a if you sign up for service The latest comes from Google Fi, offering new subscribers a Pixel 9a for free, so long as they sign up for a new plan and stick with the carrier for 24 months (via Android Authority). When it comes to plans, you have a variety of different options, with the cheapest option starting at just $10 per month. You can also join an existing family plan in order to take advantage of this promotion. There's also good news if you're an existing Fi customer, as the carrier is also offering a separate promotion for current subscribers, knocking $200 off the Pixel 9a. Of course, you'll need to have an active account with the carrier for a minimum of 120 days in order to take advantage, and make sure that any bills that come your way are paid off. For the most part, that's not all that bad if you're already using the service. Of course, as stated before, plenty of wireless carriers are offering great deals on this phone right now, like AT\u0026T offering generous payment plan options and a free pair of Pixel Buds. Verizon is giving the Pixel 9a away, along with a discount on Google services. Again, right now is going to be the perfect time to pick up the Pixel 9a, as you're going to see the best deals available during its first few weeks of release. Google Pixel 9a This is the best way to get the Pixel experience on a budget. For a limited time, Google Fi is giving away the Pixel 9a for free, so long as you stick with the carrier for 24 months.",
